# Push to Deploy

When the user says **"Push"** (or "push" or "deploy"), run these commands to deploy to Netlify:

1. `git add .`
2. `git commit -m "..."` — use a brief descriptive message (e.g., "Update river list padding") or ask the user for one
3. `git push`

Netlify is connected to the repo, so pushing automatically triggers a build and deploy. No separate deploy command is needed.
